# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DreamLab forum / Agent Control Surface — POPULATED values to MOVE INTO your .env
# Added 2026-06-11. After moving these into .env, rebuild the agentbox container
# and delete this file. These reflect the LIVE deployment; host-specific values
# (the relay URL) deliberately live here / in .env, NOT in the tracked template,
# per agentbox/CLAUDE.md "No host-project specifics in this repo".
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Agentbox NostrBridge / Agent Control Surface publish target.
# The DreamLab Cloudflare relay must be FIRST (primary); the public relays follow
# for any other bridge use. Without the dreamlab relay here, agentbox agents
# publish only to damus/primal and never reach the forum's /community/governance.
# NOTE: the agent key that SIGNS panels (AGENTBOX_PRIVKEY_HEX, already in your
# .env) must be registered in the relay's agent_registry — done for the operator
# key 11ed64225dd5e2c5e18f61ad43d5ad9272d08739d3a20dd25886197b0738663c.
NOSTR_RELAYS=wss://dreamlab-nostr-relay.solitary-paper-764d.workers.dev,wss://relay.damus.io,wss://relay.primal.net

# Xinference embedding sidecar (RuVector HNSW memory). The entrypoint now polls
# /v1/embeddings until the model is actually serving before declaring readiness,
# which fixes the cold-start window where memory stores got NULL pgvector
# embeddings (invisible to semantic search). The values below match the entrypoint
# defaults — set them only if you want to override (e.g. a slower GPU warmup).
XINFERENCE_ENDPOINT=http://xinference:9997
EMBEDDING_MODEL=bge-small-en-v1.5
XINFERENCE_WAIT_SECS=120
XINFERENCE_EMBED_WAIT_SECS=150

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# JunkieJarvis — the DreamLab forum agent (management-api/lib/junkiejarvis-agent.js).
# Rides the always-on management-api process (no supervisor program). Disabled by
# default in the tracked repo; ENABLED here for the live forum deployment.
# The JunkieJarvis identity (pubkey 2de44d5622…16e9) is whitelisted on the relay
# with the family/friends/business/agent cohorts (NOT admin) and a kind-0 name.
# Its PRIVATE key lives in .env as JUNKIEJARVIS_PRIVKEY_HEX (already set; never
# moved here, never printed). JunkieJarvis listens for gift-wrapped DMs
# (kind-1059, #p = junkiejarvis) and kind-42 channel mentions (@junkiejarvis or
# p-tag), answers with an LLM brain, and can create NIP-52 calendar events
# (kind-31923). LLM provider: set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY (preferred) or OLLAMA_BASE_URL
# elsewhere in .env; with neither set it replies a short canned apology (fail-open).
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
JUNKIEJARVIS_ENABLED=true
# Optional model override (default claude-haiku-4-5-20251001 for Anthropic).
# JUNKIEJARVIS_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
# Reply length cap in characters (JunkieJarvis keeps replies terse unless asked for detail).
JUNKIEJARVIS_MAX_REPLY=280
# Comma-separated hex pubkeys JunkieJarvis must never answer (other bots etc).
# JUNKIEJARVIS_IGNORE_PUBKEYS=

# JunkieJarvis LLM brain. Defaults to Z.AI GLM-4.5-flash (thinking disabled,
# ~2.5s) when ZAI_API_KEY is set in .env — local ollama is not on-net here.
# Override with an OpenAI-compatible gateway if desired:
#JUNKIEJARVIS_LLM_BASE=https://api.z.ai/api/paas/v4
#JUNKIEJARVIS_MODEL=glm-4.5-flash
